AGI - A man was arrested after triggering a bomb alert in the Iranian consulate a&nbsp;Paris. The police raided the diplomatic authorities on request after reporting that someone had entered the building with an explosive device. "A witness saw a man enter wearing a grenade or an explosive belt," said a police source, adding that an elite unit had been mobilized after the consulate requested surgery.&nbsp; During police intervention,&nbsp; the entire neighborhood around the consulate, in the 16th district of the capital, was closed. And also the company of Parisian transport RATP on X has announced that the traffic has been suspended on two lines of the metro that transit in the stops close to the consulate.<br> &nbsp;
